sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM), where a total volume of 33,510 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.4 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 52.8% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 6.4 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $125 strike put option expiring October 19, 2018 , with 2,400 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 240,000 underlying shares of CRM.

That number of contracts represents approximately 203,800 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 51.2% of TDG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 397,845 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $290 strike put option expiring December 20, 2019 , with 608 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 60,800 underlying shares of TDG.

That number of contracts represents approximately 1.1 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 49.8% of PNC's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.1 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $123 strike call option expiring October 12, 2018 , with 581 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 58,100 underlying shares of PNC.
